item.description:

Identified by scraper @ 2024-10-17T09:14:53+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-10-04
  • City: MINNEAPOLIS
  • State: MN
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: UNITED PARCEL SERVICE CO
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: PACKAGE WAS BROUGHT TO THE DMP BY THE RESPONDER, FROM THE BLUE SLIDE. IN THE DMP, PACKAGE WAS OPENED AND FOUND TO CONTAIN TWO, 1 GALLON METAL CANS, OF LITHCO SOLVENT, BEING SHIPPED AS A FLAMMABLE HAZ-MAT PACKAGE (UN1263, PAINT, 3, II, 1 FIBERBOARD BOX X 2 GAL). THE CAP AND SEAL ON ONE OF THE CANS, WAS DEFECTIVE, AND LEAKED A VERY SMALL AMOUNT OF THE FLAMMABLE SOLVENT, ONTO THE OUTSIDE CARTON PLUS INNER CONTAINERS. ALL PRODUCT WAS PROCESSED THROUGH THE DMP.

item.title: Report E-2024100351
item.description:
Report E-2024100351

Identified by scraper @ 2024-10-16T09:16:07+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-09-23
  • City: FRIDLEY
  • State: MN
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: XPO LOGISTICS, LLC
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: At 1511 ET, XPO-XMP notified ERTS of a cargo release. It was reported approximately 10 gallons of TRUPOWER DISHMACHINE DETERGENT ALL PURPOSE product released from 10-gallon plastic pail due to improper loading (not enough straps causing the pallet to tip over). The release impacted inside trailer#321-6238. ERTS reviewed the SDS with the caller and approved of this being cleaned up by terminal personnel, no further assistance was needed. Product was containerized into a 10-gallon poly drum, along with paper towels, oil dri, and gloves. The waste was staged for terminal personnel to manage.
